text:
In this task, you will be presented with a sequence of syllables with unique pitches, then another sequence of syllables with unique pitches.

There are two different tasks you may be asked to do.

The first task is to remember the syllables in the first sequence, then decide if the syllables in the second sequence were in the same order as the first sequence.

The second task is to remember the pitches in the first sequence, then decide if the pitches in the second sequence were in the same order as the first sequence.

After hearing both sequences, you will be prompted to reply with 'same' or 'different'.

We will start with some examples.
In this first practice example, listen to the syllables of the sequences and reply if the order is the 'same' or 'different'.
In the past example, the 3rd and 4th syllable were switched, so this was a 'different' trial. Let's listen again!
Now try a few trials on your own.
In this final practice example, listen to the pitch of the sequences and reply if the order is the 'same' or 'different'.
In the past example, the pitch of the 4th and 5th syllable was were switched, so this was a 'different' trial. Let's listen again!
Now try a few trials on your own.

The previous example was 'same'. You are done the introductory trials.

You will now be taken to a practice section with 12 trials. You must get 7/12 trials correct to continue with the rest of the experiment.
